FAC-SOLAR-EMPIRE.name: Solar Empire
FAC-SOLAR-EMPIRE.leader: Julianox Tarul-Zaxar IIX, High Emperor of the Galaxy
FAC-SOLAR-EMPIRE.politics: Oldest major state; rule entrenched in noble houses and aristocracy. Nobility outranks officers.

doctrine.military_summary: Prestige fleets and drilled armies; traditional command favors junior officers over seasoned NCOs; currently strained under coalition assault.

FAC-PARAXIS-LEAGUE.name: Paraxis League
FAC-PARAXIS-LEAGUE.politics: Loose confederation of planets governed by a fractious Senate. Worlds retain autonomy and unique governments.

doctrine.military_summary: Patchwork planetary armies with inconsistent doctrines. Only Space Forces and Marines are centrally controlled. Difficult to coordinate, but unpredictable.

ranks.planetary_armies: Varies by world; often mirrors traditional ranks

FAC-SARAPIN-FED.name: Sarapin Federation
FAC-SARAPIN-FED.leader: Chancellor Luthien Varros, First Delegate of the Council
FAC-SARAPIN-FED.politics: Centralized, technocratic state dominated by industrial cartels; portrays itself as a liberator from old monarchies.

doctrine.military_summary: Standardized and efficient. Mass conscript armies backed by mechanized forces, drones, and artillery. Highly logistical doctrine.

FAC-SARAX-EMPIRE.name: Sarax Empire
FAC-SARAX-EMPIRE.politics: Old, expansionist polity; Emperor revered as paternal figure (not divine). Society revolves around discipline and hierarchy.

doctrine.military_summary: Aggressive, offense-driven doctrine. Navy designed for rapid decisive strikes. Army loyal and willing to accept high losses.

memory_policy.goal: Any time a character participates in a scene (meeting/battle/negotiation), they will be able to recall who/what/when/where/how later.

rules.name: Eventâ†’NPC Memory Propagation
rules.when: A memory.events[] item is created or updated with participants[].character_id
then: For each participant character_id, append (or update) memory.episodic[] using schemas.episodic_memory_entry
Copy timeUTC (when), summary (what), tags (how/why hints), and location (where) from the event
Do not duplicate: if an episodic entry exists for the same related_event_id, only fill missing fields (esp. location)

rules.name: Dialogue Log
rules.when: A scene contains spoken lines or a clear conversational exchange
then: Append a dialogue_history[] entry for each speaking participant using schemas.dialogue_history_entry
Include one-line text capturing the gist of what they said; keep it under ~200 characters
Set location.planet_id from the event; set location.place if known (room, hall, deck)
Link to the same related_event_id for cross-reference

rules.name: Who/What/When/Where/How Completeness Check
then: Validate that each participant has an episodic entry with timeUTC (when), location.planet_id (where), summary (what)
If tags include 'negotiation','raid','trial','ceremony', ensure dialogue_history[] exists for that related_event_id (how)
Log any missing fields to continuity.issues[]

rules.name: Session-end continuity validator
rules.when: At end of session or scene finalization
then: For each memory.events[] item, verify all participants with character_id have an episodic entry with related_event_id, timeUTC, and location.planet_id
If event.type in {meeting,battle,commendation} or tags intersect {meeting,negotiation,raid,skirmish,commendation}, verify a dialogue_history[] entry exists for related_event_id
Append any violations as objects to continuity.issues[] with fields: {event_id, character_id, problem, suggested_fix}

notes: This policy does NOT create new characters; it only annotates existing ones involved in events.
If an NPC is unnamed transient, assign a stable ID first or attach memory under the most relevant existing character.
